<!--
    PUF Invoice Example: UC14 - BUYER AGENT + SELLER AGENT Co-Contractor Invoice

    Use Case: Sales Invoice with Both Buyer Agent and Seller Agent (Dual Agent Co-Contractor)
    Country: France (EXTENDED-CTC-FR profile)
    Format: PUF (Pagero Universal Format) 2.0
    Document Type: Standard Commercial Invoice (Type 380)
    Business Process: S6 (Co-contractor services invoice)

    Scenario Description:
    An IT services company (InfoTech Conseil Bordeaux SAS - "sous-traitant") provides
    co-contractor IT consulting services to a large enterprise (Aéronautique Toulouse SA -
    "donneur d'ordres"). A digital platform (GestionFacture360 SARL) acts as SELLER AGENT,
    managing invoice issuance on behalf of the IT subcontractor. A procurement agency
    (AchatsPro Consulting SAS) acts as BUYER AGENT, managing invoice reception, validation,
    and payment on behalf of the buyer.

    Dual Agent Co-Contractor Model:
    - SELLER (Sous-traitant IT): InfoTech Conseil Bordeaux SAS - IT services subcontractor
    - SELLER AGENT (Plateforme): GestionFacture360 SARL - Platform managing invoices for seller
    - BUYER (Donneur d'ordres): Aéronautique Toulouse SA - Principal enterprise
    - BUYER AGENT (Agence achats): AchatsPro Consulting SAS - Procurement agent for buyer

    SELLER AGENT Responsibilities:
    1. Manages invoice creation and issuance on behalf of SELLER
    2. Handles document lifecycle on PA-TR platform (emission side)
    3. Ensures regulatory compliance of invoice format
    4. Manages electronic archiving obligations for SELLER

    BUYER AGENT Responsibilities:
    1. Receives and validates invoices on behalf of BUYER
    2. Manages procurement workflow and approval
    3. Posts lifecycle statuses on PA-TR platform (reception side)
    4. Optionally pays on behalf of BUYER
    5. Manages supplier relationship for BUYER

    Key Implementation: Both Agent Parties
    - SELLER AGENT in cac:AccountingSupplierParty/cac:Party/cac:AgentParty (role code "SR")
    - BUYER AGENT in cac:AccountingCustomerParty/cac:Party/cac:AgentParty (role code "AB")

    Electronic Addressing Solution:
    - BT-49 uses format: SIREN[BUYER]_[CATEGORY]
    - "456789012_ACHATIT" routes invoice to buyer agent's PA-TR platform
    - BUYER and BUYER AGENT must use same PA-TR (or interoperability)

    Key Characteristics:
    - Invoice type 380: Standard commercial invoice
    - Business process S6: Co-contractor services invoice
    - BG-4 SELLER: IT subcontractor (InfoTech Conseil Bordeaux SAS)
    - EXT-FR-FE-BG-03 SELLER AGENT: Platform (GestionFacture360 SARL)
    - BG-7 BUYER: Principal enterprise (Aéronautique Toulouse SA)
    - EXT-FR-FE-BG-01 BUYER AGENT: Procurement agency (AchatsPro Consulting SAS)
    - BT-49: Electronic address "456789012_ACHATIT" (SIREN_ACHATIT format)
    - Total: 42,500.00 EUR

    Workflow:
    1. BUYER engages BUYER AGENT for procurement management
    2. SELLER engages SELLER AGENT for invoicing management
    3. SELLER performs co-contractor IT services for BUYER
    4. SELLER AGENT creates and issues invoice on behalf of SELLER
    5. Invoice routes to BUYER AGENT via BT-49 "456789012_ACHATIT"
    6. BUYER AGENT validates invoice and posts lifecycle statuses
    7. BUYER AGENT approves payment
    8. BUYER pays SELLER directly (or via BUYER AGENT)

    French Text Codes Used:
    - #REG# Registration information
    - #ABL# Trade register number (RCS)
    - #AAI# Additional info (dual agent co-contractor explanation)
    - #PMD# Late payment penalties
    - #PMT# Fixed collection costs
    - #BAR# Treatment type (B2B)

    Date: 2026-03-01
    Reference: XP Z12-014 Annexe A, Section 3.2.13 - Cas n°14
-->
